  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Private Business action for Biodiversity</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The global project promotes methods and instruments for biodiversity-friendly production and commercialization and systematizes the experience gained for private and public actors. After the orientation phase, in which promising approaches from agriculture and forestry (including capacity development, impact monitoring, management tools, traceability and financing instruments) were identified, the implementation phase concentrates on the exemplary testing and further development of selected methods and instruments, especially with small and medium-sized enterprises. Best practices are being further developed in Brazil, India and Mexico and policy recommendations are being derived. The project plays an important role in the mainstreaming of biodiversity in productive sectors.</narrative>
  </description>
